Silver & Gold Packages require a minimum of 2 hours before the event, while Platinum Packages require a minimum of 4 hours. When booking a wedding, the top priority is ensuring the availability of your chosen venue and church date. If you have specific dates and locations in mind, it is recommended to book at least 1 year in advance. The most critical items to cover initially are the ceremony date, preferred venue, and preferred entertainment. Once these are confirmed, the rest of the wedding planning will fall into place in due time. If you are certain about using our services, don't hesitate to book your date; some of our regular clients even secure their bookings up to 2 years in advance, particularly for certain summer dates.

Visit the Contact Us page to request the date you are looking for. We will happily respond within 24 hours, or whenever available.

After signing with us, the deposit is non-refundable. Our contracts include a 50% liability clause for your invoice. In the event of cancellation, you would owe 50% of your invoice. This policy is in place because we often reserve your date for an extended period.
